259
00:14:32.372 --> 00:14:34.433
Everything will be tip-top.

260
00:14:34.457 --> 00:14:36.561
Okay. I'm sure you'll survive
these trying times.

261
00:14:36.585 --> 00:14:39.713
so. good luck?

262
00:14:40.839 --> 00:14:43.526
Are you sure
you're a holy person?

263
00:14:43.550 --> 00:14:45.778
Yeah. I'm-I'm just.
uh. out of practice.

264
00:14:45.802 --> 00:14:48.114
I don't really bless
a lot of houses these days.

265
00:14:48.138 --> 00:14:49.991
Thank you. dear.

266
00:14:50.015 --> 00:14:52.827
I'm sure it'll be enough
to keep our family safe.

267
00:14:55.061 --> 00:14:57.105
Wow.

268
00:14:58.607 --> 00:15:00.501
Are you a wizard?

269
00:15:00.525 --> 00:15:03.254
Nah. The magic's all
in the fingers. kid.

270
00:15:05.196 --> 00:15:06.966
Wow.

271
00:15:06.990 --> 00:15:09.885
And now it's in yours.

272
00:15:09.909 --> 00:15:11.387
Whoa.

273
00:15:11.411 --> 00:15:13.598
That's real silver.
Keep it safe.

274
00:15:13.622 --> 00:15:15.474
There's a monster roaming about.

275
00:15:15.498 --> 00:15:16.851
- You mean flying.
- What's that?

276
00:15:16.875 --> 00:15:18.769
Something flew right over us.

277
00:15:18.793 --> 00:15:20.271
It knocked down
the big tree on the hill.

278
00:15:20.295 --> 00:15:24.400
We heard wings beating but
we couldn't see it in the storm.

279
00:15:24.424 --> 00:15:26.694
But it was big. Really big.

280
00:15:26.718 --> 00:15:27.927
Yeah.

281
00:15:34.476 --> 00:15:36.203
Get over here.

282
00:15:36.227 --> 00:15:38.480
Trinket found something.

283
00:15:40.065 --> 00:15:42.168
The tracks are too muddy
to discern.

284
00:15:42.192 --> 00:15:44.211
But it looks like
it took to the air

285
00:15:44.235 --> 00:15:45.820
and flew along the coast.

286
00:15:48.657 --> 00:15:50.992
Whoa.

287
00:15:52.035 --> 00:15:53.429
Think you'll be needing this.

288
00:15:53.453 --> 00:15:55.080
Ah.

289
00:16:04.589 --> 00:16:06.317
Now they look...

290
00:16:06.341 --> 00:16:07.842
human?

291
00:16:11.971 --> 00:16:14.116
It's close.

292
00:16:14.140 --> 00:16:15.767
Everyone. get ready.

293
00:16:28.697 --> 00:16:31.592
Get the fuck out.

294
00:16:31.616 --> 00:16:34.595
What. a little lamb
was behind all the mayhem?

295
00:16:34.619 --> 00:16:36.430
Oh. don't let that thing
bite you. Vex.

296
00:16:50.051 --> 00:16:51.428
Oh. fuck. oh. fuck. oh. fuck.

297
00:16:53.179 --> 00:16:54.389
Fuck!

298
00:17:27.839 --> 00:17:30.592
- I suggest we run. Right now!
- Fuck that.

299
00:17:31.593 --> 00:17:32.820
We fight!

300
00:17:34.095 --> 00:17:36.014
Grog. you dumb. brave asshole!

301
00:17:43.646 --> 00:17:46.858
Grog's down already?
Come on!

302
00:18:01.706 --> 00:18:04.685
Keyleth!
A little magic might help.

303
00:18:07.837 --> 00:18:10.173
We're in serious trouble here.

304
00:18:11.257 --> 00:18:13.778
Keyleth. snap out of it.
Keyleth!

305
00:18:13.802 --> 00:18:15.780
- Keyleth!
- Sorry. Um...

306
00:18:15.804 --> 00:18:17.096
Okay. Okay.

307
00:18:39.035 --> 00:18:41.639
Did I just make it worse?

308
00:18:50.588 --> 00:18:52.316
Look out!

309
00:19:11.067 --> 00:19:13.254
Uh. get me out.
Get-get me out!

310
00:19:13.278 --> 00:19:15.923
I'm trapped under Grog's ass!

311
00:19:17.740 --> 00:19:19.009
So...

312
00:19:19.033 --> 00:19:22.453
this is what rock bottom
feels like.

313
00:19:24.372 --> 00:19:26.183
At least we're still alive.

314
00:19:26.207 --> 00:19:27.810
thank the Everlight.

315
00:19:27.834 --> 00:19:30.771
And thanks to Keyleth
for the giant shrub.

316
00:19:30.795 --> 00:19:33.983
But did you have to make it
so thorny?

317
00:19:34.007 --> 00:19:37.027
That dragon. We almost... died.

318
00:19:38.219 --> 00:19:40.698
Except we didn't die.
Because of you. Keyleth.

319
00:19:40.722 --> 00:19:42.157
You hear me?

320
00:19:42.181 --> 00:19:44.601
We're alive because of you.

321
00:19:46.644 --> 00:19:48.831
- Grog. You're hurt.
- Nah.

322
00:19:48.855 --> 00:19:50.916
Just a flesh wound. No big.

323
00:19:50.940 --> 00:19:53.711
Question: Is this normal?

324
00:19:53.735 --> 00:19:55.796
- Oh. no. - Holy shit.
- I'm gonna throw up.

325
00:19:55.820 --> 00:19:57.339
Hold still. old friend.

326
00:19:57.363 --> 00:19:58.591
I got you.

327
00:20:04.287 --> 00:20:06.390
Oh. I feel better already.

328
00:20:06.414 --> 00:20:08.851
Thanks. Pike. You're the best.

329
00:20:08.875 --> 00:20:11.437
That... took a lot out of me.

330
00:20:11.461 --> 00:20:12.855
- I got you.
- Oh.

331
00:20:12.879 --> 00:20:15.441
Uh. thanks.

332
00:20:15.465 --> 00:20:17.318
Oh. uh. you can put me down now.

333
00:20:17.342 --> 00:20:18.903
Oh. Yeah.

334
00:20:18.927 --> 00:20:20.529
Uh... yeah.

335
00:20:20.553 --> 00:20:23.449
All right.
fuck Uriel and all of this.

336
00:20:23.473 --> 00:20:25.117
we're done here.

337
00:20:25.141 --> 00:20:27.244
We didn't sign up
for certain death.

338
00:20:27.268 --> 00:20:30.039
Must I remind you
we gave our word to the council?

339
00:20:30.063 --> 00:20:32.416
That should probably
mean something.

340
00:20:32.440 --> 00:20:34.835
Oh. who gives a soggy anus
about the council?

341
00:20:34.859 --> 00:20:38.297
The only word I care about
is "Scanlan Shorthalt."

342
00:20:38.321 --> 00:20:40.257
And yes.
I know that's two words.

343
00:20:40.281 --> 00:20:42.259
but you know what I'm saying.

344
00:20:42.283 --> 00:20:45.179
Yeah. What have those
fuckity-fucks ever done for us?

345
00:20:45.203 --> 00:20:47.431
Except give us a job
and a bunch of gold

346
00:20:47.455 --> 00:20:49.433
and treasure and stuff?

347
00:20:49.457 --> 00:20:51.644
We've fought a lot of things...

348
00:20:51.668 --> 00:20:52.978
but a dragon?

349
00:20:53.002 --> 00:20:54.730
An actual dragon?

350
00:20:54.754 --> 00:20:56.941
It's not about the council.

351
00:20:56.965 --> 00:20:59.151
or the contract...
it's about these people.

352
00:20:59.175 --> 00:21:00.527
They need us.

353
00:21:00.551 --> 00:21:02.780
We can't just run away.

354
00:21:02.804 --> 00:21:05.199
This is why I hate traveling
with holy people.

355
00:21:05.223 --> 00:21:07.576
- They're too goddamned good.
- Pike...

356
00:21:07.600 --> 00:21:09.954
this creature is beyond us.

357
00:21:09.978 --> 00:21:12.456
When Vex and I were young.

358
00:21:12.480 --> 00:21:14.583
one of those monsters
killed our mother.

359
00:21:14.607 --> 00:21:17.211
I've studied dragons
my entire life. hoping to find

360
00:21:17.235 --> 00:21:18.379
the one that did it.

361
00:21:18.403 --> 00:21:19.546
I can...

362
00:21:19.570 --> 00:21:21.423
feel when they're close.

363
00:21:21.447 --> 00:21:24.218
A horrid pain in my head.

364
00:21:24.242 --> 00:21:25.719
Then it's settled.

365
00:21:25.743 --> 00:21:27.972
We'll go back to the palace
and get out of the contract.

366
00:21:27.996 --> 00:21:29.765
You don't understand. Percy.

367
00:21:29.789 --> 00:21:32.101
I felt it there. too.
at the palace.

368
00:21:32.125 --> 00:21:34.103
Y-You're just
telling us this now?

369
00:21:34.127 --> 00:21:35.854
I'm sorry. I...

370
00:21:35.878 --> 00:21:38.190
I wasn't certain
until the dragon...

371
00:21:38.214 --> 00:21:40.567
It's been years since Mother...

372
00:21:40.591 --> 00:21:42.194
Are you sure. Vex'ahlia?

373
00:21:42.218 --> 00:21:44.363
I know what I felt.
Someone on the council

374
00:21:44.387 --> 00:21:47.074
must have been in contact
with the dragon. or...

375
00:21:47.098 --> 00:21:50.911
I don't know.
but I-I'm sure it was real.

376
00:21:50.935 --> 00:21:53.372
Then we walk away
from all of this.

377
00:21:53.396 --> 00:21:55.791
It's not worth it.
You heard her.

378
00:21:55.815 --> 00:21:58.544
One of them might be working
with that monster.

379
00:21:58.568 --> 00:22:00.629
Let's just get
the hell out of here

380
00:22:00.653 --> 00:22:03.882
and never set foot
in Emon again.

381
00:22:03.906 --> 00:22:06.385
Can we all agree on that?

382
00:22:49.243 --> 00:22:51.496
Oh. no.

383
00:22:53.456 --> 00:22:57.668
They wiped them out.
all of them.

384
00:23:44.215 --> 00:23:46.425
Pike! Get over here!

385
00:23:50.346 --> 00:23:52.074
Please. Everlight.

386
00:23:52.098 --> 00:23:54.076
let your power reach him.

387
00:23:54.100 --> 00:23:55.744
Pike. Please.

388
00:23:55.768 --> 00:23:57.371
Shit!

389
00:23:57.395 --> 00:23:59.748
No. I can't do it.

390
00:23:59.772 --> 00:24:02.400
I'm still too weak from before.

391
00:24:13.161 --> 00:24:14.745
We could have stopped this.

392
00:24:15.788 --> 00:24:17.415
Should have.

393
00:24:24.797 --> 00:24:26.525
What the hell
are you doing. Scanlan?

394
00:24:26.549 --> 00:24:29.736
Thinking of a rhyme
for "dead dragon."

395
00:24:29.760 --> 00:24:31.321
'Cause I...

396
00:24:31.345 --> 00:24:33.323
I guess we're killing one.

397
00:24:33.347 --> 00:24:35.075
I'm in.

398
00:24:35.099 --> 00:24:38.495
Uh. I mean I'm not gonna lie.
I'm terrified out of my mind.

399
00:24:38.519 --> 00:24:39.955
But I'm in.

400
00:24:39.979 --> 00:24:42.457
I don't like losin'...

401
00:24:42.481 --> 00:24:46.211
but now I'm feelin' things.
on the inside.

402
00:24:46.235 --> 00:24:49.006
They don't feel right.

403
00:24:49.030 --> 00:24:52.134
So yeah. I'm with ya.

404
00:24:52.158 --> 00:24:53.385
That was...

405
00:24:53.409 --> 00:24:55.512
actually well stated. Grog.

406
00:24:55.536 --> 00:24:57.514
- What was?
- Uh. never mind.

407
00:24:57.538 --> 00:24:59.433
Count me in as well.

408
00:24:59.457 --> 00:25:01.018
You guys...

409
00:25:01.042 --> 00:25:02.644
we're doing this.

410
00:25:02.668 --> 00:25:05.856
You all realize we're going
to die a truly horrible death.

411
00:25:05.880 --> 00:25:07.256
Perhaps. sister.

412
00:25:08.299 --> 00:25:10.986
But we'll die gloriously.

413
00:25:11.010 --> 00:25:13.989
and we'll kill a fucking dragon.

414
00:26:07.900 --> 00:26:09.860
Chirp.

414
00:26:10.305 --> 00:27:10.581
